# Revisions to skip when running `git blame`.
#
# Bulk reformats only — commits that changed how the code looks and nothing
# about what it does. Without this, blame on almost every line points here
# instead of at the change that actually introduced the logic.
#
# GitHub honours this file automatically. Locally, opt in once with:
#
#   git config blame.ignoreRevsFile .git-blame-ignore-revs
#
# Add the full 40-character hash of the reformat commit below once it exists.
# A short hash or a missing commit makes git blame fail outright, so add it
# only after committing.

